Bank of Italy to Divest 300 Million-Euro Real Estate Portfolio

-- B y   S h a r o n   S m y t h   a n d   S i m o n   P a c k a r d
-- 
2011-04-21T10:58:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-21/bank-of-italy-to-divest-300-million-euro-real-estate-portfolio.html
The  Bank of Italy  has hired
Colliers International Italia and Exitone SpA as advisers on the
sale of a real estate portfolio valued at more than 300 million
euros ($439 million).  The portfolio consists of 240,000 square meters (2.58
million square feet) of bank branches and residential properties
around  Italy , Colliers International, the world’s third-largest
commercial real estate services company, said in an e-mailed
statement today.  The assets include “prestigious buildings located in major
Italian cities,” Colliers said, without being more specific.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Sharon Smyth in Madrid at 
